According to the Spokesperson of the command, SP Gambo Isah, in a statement on Friday, said that the suspect was arrested on Wednesday, after he swapped the ATM card of a victim.  .
. Gambo further stated that the police recovered 30 ATM cards of different banks and a Honda Accord car from the suspect. “On the March 30, based on a tip off, the command succeeded in arresting one Hussaini Suleiman alias Khalifa, 19, of Zoo road Kano, Kano state, a notorious serial fr@udster that specialized in swapping ATM cards of unsuspecting members of the public at ATM points.
